## Troubleshooting

**"Port 5432 already in use"**
You have a local PostgreSQL running. Either stop it (`brew services stop postgresql`) or change the port in `docker-compose.yml`.

**"Port 8080 already in use"**
Another service is using 8080. Either stop it or start the training app on a different port: `SERVER_PORT=8081 ./mvnw spring-boot:run`

**"jcmd: command not found"**
Your JDK's `bin` directory isn't on your PATH. Either add it or use the full path: `/path/to/jdk-21/bin/jcmd`

**VisualVM shows no process**
Make sure VisualVM is using the same JDK as the app. Launch with: `visualvm --jdkhome $JAVA_HOME`

**"docker-compose: command not found"**
Docker Desktop v2+ uses `docker compose` (no hyphen). Try: `docker compose up -d`

**App starts but /api/rewards returns empty**
The seed data may not have loaded. Check logs for Liquibase migration output. If needed, run manually: `docker exec -i <postgres-container> psql -U loyalty loyalty < data/seed-data.sql`

---

## What's Next

Session 1 starts with the app running on the default (healthy) profile. You'll inspect the JVM using `jcmd` and VisualVM, and build a baseline picture of what "healthy" looks like.

Before Session 1, make sure you can:
- [ ] `docker-compose up -d` starts PostgreSQL and Kafka
- [ ] `./mvnw spring-boot:run` starts the app
- [ ] `curl localhost:8080/actuator/health` returns UP
- [ ] `jcmd` shows the loyalty-service process
- [ ] VisualVM connects to the process

If any of these fail, reach out to the training coordinator before the session.

